HEADWORD: Cinquecento
<hw>Cin`que*cen"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. & a.</pos> <ety>[It.,
five hundred, abbrev. for fifteen hundred. The <ets>Cinquecento</ets>
style was so called because it arose after the year 1500.]</ety>
<def>The sixteenth century, when applied to Italian art or literature;
<as>as, the sculpture of the <ex>Cinquecento</ex>; <ex>Cinquecento</ex>
style</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

